                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d787">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Commanding General of the United States Army Forces in the
                        Far East</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacArthur</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Chief of Staff</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Marshall</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="44" type="source" xml:id="d787fn44">Copy of telegram
                        obtained from the Franklin D. Roosevelt Library, Hyde Park, N. Y.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Fort Mills</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-02-12">February 12,
                            1942</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>262. The following message is from President Quezon: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“The President of the United States:</p>
                        <p>I wish to thank you for your prompt answer to the proposal which I
                            submitted to you with the unanimous approval of my war cabinet. We fully
                            appreciate the reasons upon which your decision is based and we are
                            abiding by it.</p>
                        <p rend="right">(signed) Quezon.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacArthur</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
